  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>An L shape can be subdivided into four smaller L shapes. In each successive subdivision, every L shape is replaced by four smaller L’s in fixed relative positions such that exactly one of these is oriented the same way as the original L shape. After 2005 successive subdivisions the total number of L’s is 4^(2005). How many of these L’s are in the same orientation as the original?</denoised_question>",
