  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>Find the x-intercept of the line with equation y = 2x - 6 after it is translated upward by 4 units.</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "1. Start with the original line: y = 2x - 6.\\n2. Translate the line upward by 4 units by adding 4 to the y-value: y = 2x - 6 + 4 which simplifies to y = 2x - 2.\\n3. The x-intercept is found by setting y = 0. Therefore, solve 0 = 2x - 2.\\n4. Add 2 to both sides: 2 = 2x.\\n5. Divide both sides by 2: x = 1.\\n6. Thus, the x-intercept of the resulting line is 1 (or at the point (1, 0)).",
  "final_answer": "<answer>(1, 0)</answer>"
}

