  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>Consider all questions on this contest that ask for a single real-valued answer (excluding question 887). Let M be the median of these answers. Estimate M.</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "1. First, we remove all sentences that are unrelated to the math problem (such as the coffee shop anecdotes) to isolate the relevant portion.\\n2. The cleaned problem asks us to consider the collection of all questions on a contest that have a single real-valued answer (with one particular question, number 887, excluded).\\n3. Let M denote the median of these answers. The task is to \"estimate M.\"\\n4. However, no numerical details, distribution information, or list of answers is provided that could be used to compute or even approximate the median value M. Without additional quantitative data, no effective estimation of the median can be performed.\\n5. Therefore, based solely on the information available, we conclude that the problem does not supply enough data to determine an estimate for M.",
  "final_answer": "<answer>Insufficient information to estimate M.</answer>"
